	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Necromancer 1 - 45</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Vital</a> | 
		            5/22/2000 4:02:34 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">   1-5 Hunt in Your newbie area.<BR>
   5-12 Ok, just kill Orc raiders and Puma's maybe, until you reach lvl 8, after you get your spells, just solo The Giant spiders and Sand Scarbs or anything else that or anything that is Yellow or low red. Ok, now for those who don't know how to solo good with a Necromancer, I will tell you. Start of by casting your DoT (Damage over Time) spell on it to pull it, then tell your pet to attack, cast your clinging darknes spell to make it nice and slow and just fear it and keep it feared and cast your DoTs back on it if they wear off.<BR>
   12-20 Go to the Oasis- The loot here sucks, but the exp is great, at lvl 12 just kill Caimans and Crocs maybe, and once you get to 14 or 15 you can try some Dw Caimans but at your own risk, they are tough w/out you lvl 16 pet. Ok, at 16 you just solo caimans, crocs, DW caimans but I wouldnt try Dw Crocs yet, wait untill you are lvl 18 and then start killing DW crocs too untill you are lvl 20.<BR>
(DW means Deep Water for all of you who havn't been to the Oasis before.)<BR>
   20-29 Go to South Karana and I would say get into a Aviak group untill you are lvl 24, and then just solo what all the Aviaks you want just don't try the Aviak Avocents because they are tough.<BR>
Once you get to lvl 25 I what I did was I just always made sure I had sow and soloed as normal, just I also killed Aviak Avocents too, (note at this lvl they are red and you won't be able to kill them with out kiting them) Just cast Heat blood and then cast Engulfing darknes (if he resists engulfing don't worry about trying to cast it agian, you will need the mana.) Then send your pet in and cast Shock of Poison spell, and that should piss the Avocent off, if not cast it again, then he will start running after you, just RUN and he won't pay any attention to your pet so you will be geting free hits in with you pet wile you run. Once you get far enough away, cast Shock of Poison again and repeat untill dead. (The Avocent almost always kills your pet, also I forgot to mention that you will need to cast Allure of Death spell on your self before the fight, and you will also have to use your life tap spell a few times in the fight with the Avocent just to stay alive.) Loot on these is 1-3pp or so and some times they drop Black Perals!! Which sell for around 200pp,<BR>
   29-35 Go to sister island and solo those chicks ) They aren't that hard and are great exp, loot is almost nothing to 4pp and they almost always drop a purity belt which sells for 1pp.<BR>
   35-?? Go to your favorite town FREE PORT ) and head to the arena and once you get in the arena you will see some NPC walking around in all Armor named Jakom somthing (forgot the last name) ok, this is what you do, you will see a litte porch spot (the checkerd area) go under there and make you pet and all that other good stuff, ok, cast Call to Bones on your self and pull him with Vampirc Curse, then cast Engulfing Darknes, NOT Dooming Darknes for many reasons, trust me, if he resists, oh well, doesn't really matter ) just helps out a bit if he doesn't. Of next cast Venom of the Snake on him, then when he gets close to you run around, go up the stairs and back around, (but now you are on the top) and once he gets close to you up there just hope down, and because he is a stupid NPC he won't jump down after you, insted he will run alllll the way back around and down the stairs, this will give you time to recast DoTs such as Vampiric Curse/Venom of the Snake/Boil Blood what ever.. and if you have him fully DoTed and he is on your pet, nuke his ass, you don't want him on your pet, he will kill it in like 5 seconds, no kidding. loot 1-4pp and drops FS weapons and Ring Mail Peices sometimes. A friend of mine is still hunting this guy and he's lvl 47 and he says it's good exp so.. If you have any questions or didn't quite understand some of the info I have stated up here, just go make a Chr. on the server Sol Ro. and just send me a tell, Names Vital and yes I am only lvl 19, or I might be higher when you see me ) But I do have another chr that is Necromancer and he's lvl 35, just I made him a Human and I'm redoing him =) 
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
