				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Xemitel is wrong, the 2 Guild-master wont aggro if you stay in the close area zone (on the fisrt and second lvl).<BR>
What i've done is the folowing.<BR>
<BR>
No pet! you wont need it at all.. ;)<BR>
<BR>
Jacom usulaay spawn in the left side of arena so go to the right side and  half the way of the 2nd edge. There root him as soon as it spawn, Darkness him and scourge or VoS him and sit down and med. Re-root and reDOT as needed.<BR>
<BR>
If he is darnessed, you will have time to recast root 3 times before he comes to you.<BR>
<BR>
When he is too close just jump down to fisrt edge of arena (dont fall IN arena! its messy and getting out will pull the 2 others located inside)<BR>
You will then see him make all the way back to the stairs to go to fisrt edge. reroot and dot or DD at will. Keep darkness on and when root breaks reroot (you have 2 chances befor he comes to you) and go to the opposite side of arena before recasting ..<BR>
<BR>
Easy kills and decent loot.<BR>
<BR>
in the med time you can work on your skills..<BR>
<BR>
Good luck.<BR>
<BR>
Ho BTW this will ruin your faction with North FP guards.. to get it back just head to newbies zone in WFP, and go see Ping the gnome merchant near tent. buy all the picks the newbies sell to him and head to EFP in bad zone in the inn there is a guy that will give you good faction, exp and a lotto ticket for 4 picks.<BR>
kill every orc you see to to gain faction back.. 
